items.title: IT Q3 earnings season begins on a strong note as TCS, HCL Tech top estimates
items.description: IT sector's Q3 results show a positive start, with TCS and HCL Technologies exceeding revenue and profit expectations. HCL Tech recorded a nine-quarter high in new order bookings, while TCS maintained strong deal flow. Despite sustained new deals, TCS faces a revenue growth deceleration, raising concerns about deal ramp-up amid client delays.

items.title: Infosys Q3 results preview: PAT, revenue may grow by up to 9% YoY; FY26 guidance, deals pipeline in focus
items.description: Infosys' Q3 results are anticipated to show modest growth, with brokerages predicting a slight uptick in net profit and revenue. While near-term momentum might be tempered by seasonal factors, the focus will be on management's outlook for FY26, deal execution, and client spending trends amidst global economic uncertainties.

items.title: ICICI Prudential Life Q3 Results: PAT jumps 19% YoY to Rs 397 crore, net premium income drops 4%
items.description: ICICI Prudential Life reported a 19% YoY rise in Q3 PAT to Rs 387 crore even as net premium income fell 3.7%. VNB touched Rs 615 crore with strong margins, while AUM grew 6.5%. Retail protection APE surged over 40%, supported by GST reforms and rising policy volumes.

items.title: Bank of Maharashtra Q3 Results: Net profit rises 26.5% YoY to Rs 1,779 crore, NII jumps 16%
items.description: Bank of Maharashtra posted a 26.5% year-on-year rise in Q3FY26 net profit to ₹1,779 crore, supported by strong operating performance and better asset quality. Net interest income grew 16.3% to ₹7,344 crore, while return on assets improved to 1.86%.

items.title: Bank of Maharashtra reports 26% YoY jump in profit to Rs 1,779 crore
items.description: Bank of Maharashtra posted a 26% rise in Q3 profit, supported by strong loan growth and improved asset quality. The lender declared a 10% interim dividend, maintained a healthy NIM, and reported robust corporate loan demand, with advances and deposits continuing to expand at a steady pace.

items.title: ICICI Lombard posts lower quarterly profit as commissions, employee costs rise
items.description: India's ICICI Lombard ​General Insurance reported a decline in third-quarter profit on Tuesday, ⁠as higher payouts to agents and employees outweighed strong demand in retail health and motor insurance.

items.title: Tata Elxsi Q3 profit falls 45% on one-time labour code charge
items.description: Indian engineering research and development (ER&D) firm ‍Tata Elxsi reported a ​45.3% drop in third-quarter profit on ⁠Tuesday, primarily due to a one-time charge tied to the country's new labour codes.
